@SenDuckworth and I are working together as the only two Illinois members of Congress on the Senate and House Armed Services Committees to deliver for the men and women working at the Rock Island Arsenal.

Proud to share that we’re close to delivering bipartisan legislation with the rest of the Quad Cities lawmakers that will help protect their essential jobs.

https://t.co/wkxPfjNEdq

BIG NEWS for IL-17!

@AmeriCorps has awarded nearly $100,000 to Highland Community College Foundation in Freeport to support older adults making a difference in our community.

Proud to see this investment in our future! https://t.co/W49vltzlBj

Every LGBTQ child should be able to grow up to fulfill their dreams of serving our country.

@SecDef renaming the USS Harvey Milk and singling out LGBTQ service members who bravely serve our country is disgusting and un-American.

So I called him out on it: https://t.co/9ChhlxQIdD

We are nearing the midpoint of severe weather season in the Midwest. 

@NWS offices must have the resources to keep us safe from thunderstorms, flash floods, hurricanes, and tornadoes. 

I’m working with my colleagues across the aisle to support meteorologists from DOGE cuts that would destroy the weather forecasting enterprise. Thanks NWS Quad Cities for the tour!

@ElonMusk and @WhiteHouse are continuing to charge ahead with their sledgehammer approach to critical funding.

Next on the chopping block for them: eliminating HIV prevention funding at the CDC which helps save lives.

I’m joining a fight with my colleagues to make sure this funding isn’t cut-off and the CDC’s cutting-edge research can continue to keep us all safer.

As a meteorologist, when severe weather happened it was all hands on deck.

Now in Congress, after 2 devastating hurricanes, it’s time to care for our neighbors.

@SpeakerJohnson needs to do the right thing &amp; call Congress back. Full statement ⬇️ https://t.co/h5dz54xXkl
